## ============================================================
## 1. Introduction
## ============================================================

- SCHC is a compression and fragmentation mechanism defined in
- [RFC8724] while [RFC9363] provides a YANG Data Model for formal
- representation of SCHC Rules used either for compression/
- decompression (C/D) or fragmentation/reassembly (F/R).  The
- inappropriate changes to SCHC Rules leads to some possible attacks.
- The goal of this document is to define a augmentation to the existing
- Data Model in order to restrict the changes in the rules and,
- therefore, the impact of possible attacks.
+ SCHC is a compression and fragmentation mechanism defined in
+ [RFC8724] while [RFC9363] provides a YANG Data Model for formal
+ representation of SCHC Rules used either for compression/
+ decompression (C/D) or fragmentation/reassembly (F/R).  The SCHC
+ Architecture [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture] organizes a SCHC deployment
+ into Endpoints, Instances, Contexts (each a Set of Rules together with
+ metadata), Sessions, and Domains.  Inappropriate changes to SCHC Rules
+ lead to some possible attacks.  The goal of this document is to define
+ an augmentation to the existing Data Model in order to restrict the
+ changes in the Rules and, therefore, the impact of possible attacks.

