+ This document uses the following terms, aligned with the SCHC
+ Architecture [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture]:
+
+ Access Control:  The set of restrictions that limit which Rules, field
+    descriptors, and Rule elements of a Context may be added, removed,
+    or modified.  These restrictions are expressed as metadata carried
+    in the SCHC Data Model [RFC9363]; in the terminology of
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture], they form part of the metadata of a
+    Context (a Set of Rules together with metadata).
+
+ Management request processing:  A NETCONF [RFC6241], RESTCONF
+    [RFC8040], or CORECONF [I-D.ietf-core-comi] request is processed and
+    applied to the Context used by a SCHC Instance.  In
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture] this write path is the Context
+    Provisioning, Synchronization, and Configuration Distribution
+    performed by the Domain's management entities.
+
+ Rule Manager (RM):  The management function that applies Rule
+    modifications to the Context used by an Endpoint's Instances,
+    subject to the Access Control defined in this document.  It
+    corresponds to the combination of the Instance Manager (per-Endpoint
+    apply and synchronization) and the Domain Manager and Context
+    Repository (Domain-scoped ownership of Contexts) of
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture].
+
+ Context / Set of Rules (SoR):  As defined in
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture], a Context is a Set of Rules together
+    with metadata.  The access rights defined in this document are part
+    of that metadata and apply to the Rules of the SoR.

